Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.32,1:19:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is more the conventional you might say\Nultra-conservative. you only get if you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.04,1:19:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,produce.\NAnd uh them the maternal is more like
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.52,1:19:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,classically socialism. Everybody gets\Nsupported no matter what and uh gets a
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.80,1:19:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,pay paycheck every month even if they're\Nin prison at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.67,1:19:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And they worry about the voting rights\Nof prisoners. Here's a guy in there for
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.28,1:19:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,stabbing six people to death, rapving\Nhis mother-in-law, theft and thievery
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.71,1:19:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and drug dealing. And they're worrying\Nabout his getting the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.76,1:19:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Worrying about his right to vote.\NUh yes. Okay. That's what you call an
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.67,1:20:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,ideologist. It cannot differentiate the\Nthe idea of freedom and equality from
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.19,1:20:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,all from the reality of when it is\Nreally grossly inappropriate and not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.15,1:20:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,really applicable. You know what I'm\Nsaying? I don't know that I want to
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.08,1:20:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,trust the judge moral judgment of a guy\Nwho's in there for uh kidnapping and
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.64,1:20:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,three three murders as well as burglary\Nand drug dealing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.52,1:20:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I I was supposed to value his\Nvote in the presidential election
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.64,1:20:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in presidential election. It's\Nhysterical.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.84,1:20:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the confusion then of\Nthe ideational with the with the real is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.32,1:20:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes it out of context. So a sense\Nof reality then is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.19,1:20:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,not just content but content within a\Ncertain context.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.92,1:20:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had a chart a slide we were going\Nto show this morning but we ran out of
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.08,1:20:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,time on the relationship between content\Nand context.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.80,1:21:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The sophisticated person above 200\Nrealizes that morality depends on not
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.56,1:21:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just on content but on the context.\NSo whether certain things are ethical or
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.00,1:21:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,not\Ncannot be answered when separated from
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.56,1:21:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the context in which they went on. So we\Ngave as an example in previous lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.19,1:21:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is unethical in peace and war\Ncannot be compared because there the
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.84,1:21:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,context is differently whether the\Ngovernment can check your email or not
Dialogue: 0,1:21:35.36,1:21:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is against uh human American tradition\Nin times of peace in times of war
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.56,1:21:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whether there's somebody set to blow up\Nyour entire city
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.80,1:21:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then that's a different context. So\Nwhat's immoral in one context becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.96,1:22:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,moral or even necessary in another. So\Nyou might say the government would be
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.15,1:22:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,negligent to not do so in a time of war\Nin an electronic age when all the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.63,1:22:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,communication of what's about to get\Nblown up and who's going to blow it up
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.28,1:22:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is transmitted electronically\Nthat the government to be moral would be
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.32,1:22:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ethically required to monitor such\Nthings to safeguard the life of the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.36,1:22:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,citizens.\NSo whether a thing is true or false,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.36,1:22:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's moral or immoral, whether\Nit's ethical cannot be decided
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.52,1:22:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you state in what context\Nyou see in what context is this. So in
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.48,1:22:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what context is this moral or immoral?\NThe confusion of ideology with its
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.88,1:22:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,actual reality in human existence\Nis a refinement.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.71,1:22:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now\Nhaving said that we we are perhaps more
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.28,1:23:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,able to\Num allow others to differ from us.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.12,1:23:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right to for others to differ\Nwith us. I always say everybody has the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.48,1:23:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,right to be wrong.\NAll of the people who disagree with
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.96,1:23:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,everything I'm saying have a perfect\Nright to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.08,1:23:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are they?\NCamera. Camera. Camera. The cameras are
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.56,1:23:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,flashing. And we'll of course compare\Nthat later and find out who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.80,1:23:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See that it's reported to the proper\Nauthorities.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.19,1:23:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the value freedom. Then we see that all\Nof life is beautiful. All of life is
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.08,1:23:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,divine.\NSo we stop picking that this is holier.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.15,1:23:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more beautifuler. This is more\Nanything than anything else. We see
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.48,1:24:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually what dawns on us as an\Nillumination from inside
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.36,1:24:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.52,1:24:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty and perfection. uh of all that\Nexists and it comes as a revelation much
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.60,1:24:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,like the light came into the room uh\Nwhen you realize the divinity of all
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.71,1:24:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that exists.\NI remember going through what has been
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.88,1:24:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,classically called the final doorway of\Nin which I laid down as a barrier
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.23,1:24:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,between myself and the realization of\NGod
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.23,1:24:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,um existence itself life and I gave I\Nsaid the one thing I have not
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.88,1:24:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendered to God is life itself that I\Nstill have the illusion that I I am the
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.48,1:24:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,source of my the ongoingness of my life\Nand So I lay that down. And as I lay
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.88,1:25:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,down, owning myself is the source of\Nlife, a great terror overcame me.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.71,1:25:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably the worst anxiety I've ever\Nexperienced.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.40,1:25:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was terror at a great existential\Ndepth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.84,1:25:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And to get through it was was almost\Nimpossible. I'd seen a couple of people
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.48,1:25:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,been through it. I saw Jesus Christ went\Nthrough it. I saw Buddha went through
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.52,1:25:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NYou could see the few people who have
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.71,1:25:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,been through. It was like a high pass\Nand I began to pull back from it and as
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.88,1:25:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I say a terror of great great extent a\Ngreater terror than I had ever
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.19,1:25:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced before and then came forth a\Nteaching from within my knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.44,1:25:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This too is illusion. All fear is\Nillusion. And I surrendered this fear
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.76,1:25:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that if I let go only myself is the\Nsource of ex existence and life uh that
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.00,1:25:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I would expire forever die forever. So\Nthe terror of non-existence existence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.15,1:26:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,versus non-existence\Nuh arose and I put my faith in those
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.56,1:26:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that knowingness. I put my faith in the\Nabsolute knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.76,1:26:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is illusion. All fear is\Nillusion. All fear is illusion. So I put
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.19,1:26:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,my faith in that premise.\NThank God it was true.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.36,1:26:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time you didn't know whether it\Nwas true. You only had faith in whether
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.40,1:26:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it was true. And the faith came from the\Npower of the knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.15,1:26:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does an advanced guru teach?\NWhat happens with the with those of
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.23,1:26:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced teaching is that knowingness is\Nconveyed via
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.63,1:26:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,via the the atheric body, the energy\Nfield of the knowingness of the teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.12,1:27:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to the atheric body of the student.\NNot the content of it had nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:27:07.04,1:27:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with that, but the absolute faith and\Nconviction and power of it. So somewhere
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.76,1:27:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,in past lives, there had been a teacher\Nof an extraordinarily high caliber
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.40,1:27:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,because the knowingness was like\Nconcrete and cement that I could trust
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.96,1:27:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it. But even then as I turned my life\Nover uh to this this teaching that all
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.63,1:27:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,feel all fear is illusion. And I let go.\NI let go. I stopped holding back. And
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.19,1:27:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror did arise. And the terror was\Nfrankly to tell you severe. the terror
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.44,1:27:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of throughout all the ages, all the\Nlifetimes, all the embodiment, all the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.67,1:28:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,karmic evolutions\Nuh all came now to this one final point.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:01.19,1:28:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And so now\Nthat came out of not out of memory but
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.44,1:28:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the energy field of the\Nconsciousness of the teacher. It comes
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.88,1:28:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,about as a nonlinear nonverbal\Nenergy field which is in within the oh
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.23,1:28:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it's within the aura of the teacher.\NYes. Okay. So that which we convey today
Dialogue: 0,1:28:26.96,1:28:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is within the aura field of the teacher\Nand it's an historic event.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.92,1:28:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell you now\Nall fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.04,1:28:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself knew it. Then I lived through\Nthe truth of it. And therefore I tell
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.84,1:28:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you with the conviction above of the\Nabsolute
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.63,1:29:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that all fear is illusion.\NNo death is possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.08,1:29:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you Lord God\Nfor the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.28,1:29:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,authority\Nto make this statement to these
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.40,1:29:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,students. So I take responsibility for\Nthat statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.96,1:29:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I take responsibility for the truth of\Nthat statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.60,1:29:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I'm wrong,\NI'll never admit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.00,1:29:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be long gone dead. And you won't\Neven remember
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.08,1:29:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who was that so that lied to me back\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.71,1:29:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My name will be obliterated in your\Nminds. And
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.28,1:29:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,some idiot back there somewhere said\Nall fear is illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.28,1:29:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is problematic. All fear is a\Nconjecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.67,1:30:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All fear is a conjecture. It's a\Nconstruction.
